SIMPLE: fishy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fishy
<hw>Fish"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting
of fish; fishlike; having the qualities or taste of fish; abounding in
fish.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Extravagant, like some stories about catching fish;
improbable; also, rank or foul.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>

<--3. creating suspicion that the surface appearances are misleading -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fisk</ent>⟦br⟧
